@page "/privacy"

<PageTitle>Privacy</PageTitle>

<section class="hero-panel hero-panel-compact">
    <span class="eyebrow">Privacy And Scope</span>
    <h1>This sample keeps everything local.</h1>
    <p class="lead mb-0">
        The counter state is stored in a local singleton service for the running application only. No database, external API, or third-party JavaScript is required.
    </p>
</section>

<section class="card-grid">
    <article class="info-card">
        <h2>Local State</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>The counter resets when the app restarts.</li>
            <li>No user account data is collected.</li>
            <li>The sample is designed only for classroom learning.</li>
        </ul>
    </article>

    <article class="info-card">
        <h2>Teaching Focus</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>The goal is to introduce Blazor components and event handling.</li>
            <li>SignalR transport is handled automatically by Blazor Server.</li>
            <li>Students can focus on C# and UI state rather than manual JavaScript wiring.</li>
        </ul>
    </article>
</section>
